description:
&lt;p&gt;Internal applicants only need apply&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Learning Partner Team within Corporate Nursing, Midwifery and Allied Health Professions are looking for an Innovative and motivated individual to join their team and be responsible for managing and providing a comprehensive, effective and professional administrative support service to the Learning Partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will lead on the management of training information in relation to Continuous Professional Development (CPD), Continuous Workforce Development (CWD) requests and oversea the collation and administration of the Trust wide Training matrix and Training Needs analysis (TNA).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will work collaboratively with the learning partner team, key stakeholders and will have a detailed understanding of Learning &amp; Funding rules and regulations, the Learning Partner role and have a focus on internal and external training providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will manage the Learning &amp; Funding Administration Assistant and provide support and cross cover to the wider teams within Learning and Education where appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alongside all of the above you will have excellent communication and organisational skills, the ability to multi-task, work under pressure, thrive on being part of a team, whilst producing work that is reliable and accurate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who will be proactive, and have the confidence to deal with anything with enthusiasm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please read the Job Description and Person Specification attached, and ensure that your statement in support of your application reflects these criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information on this post or an informal discussion, please contact: theanna.desancho@nhs.net, Nursing &amp; Midwifery Learning Partner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this post will close at sufficient applicants&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTheanna De SanchoJob titleNursing &amp; Midwifery Learning PartnerEmail addresstheanna.desancho@nhs.netTelephone number01642 850850 ext. 57157&lt;/p&gt;
